{
  "directives": {
    "diabetes": "ICMR-NIN 2024 Type-2 Diabetes protocol: Strictly cap total carbohydrates at a maximum of 45-50% of total daily energy intake. Eliminate rapid-acting simple sugars (jaggery, honey, sweets) and refined grains (maida, white rice). Prioritize low-GI, fiber-dense local complex carbohydrates including whole millets (ragi, jowar, bajra) and whole pulses (chana, moong).",
    "hypertension": "South Asian Cardiovascular DASH Protocol: Limit daily salt intake strictly to less than 5 grams per day (approximately 2300mg Sodium). Explicitly eliminate hidden high-sodium Indian culinary staples including commercial pickles (achaar), papads, salted namkeens, and instant spice mixes.",
    "pcos": "Insulin-Sensitizing & Anti-Inflammatory Framework: Target insulin resistance using low-GI complex carbohydrates paired with bioavailable proteins and local omega-3 fats (walnuts, flaxseeds, chia seeds). Restrict heavy loads of unfermented commercial soy to support hormonal equilibrium.",
    "gerd": "Indian Gastric Acid Reflux Management: Eliminate severe mucosal irritants common in Indian cooking, specifically green and red chillies, raw onions, garlic, and heavy garam masala blends. Ban strong carminatives like pudina (mint) and high-volume triggers like deep-fried foods and commercial chai/coffee.",
    "fatty_liver": "NAFLD Hepatic Lipid Management: Absolute zero tolerance for alcohol and trans-fats like Vanaspati/Dalda common in commercial frying. Restrict simple sugars and processed confectionery to halt hepatic fat accumulation. Maximize local MUFAs (mustard oil, groundnut oil) and antioxidant-rich vegetables.",
    "chronic_kidney_disease": "CRITICAL CKD PRECAUTION: Restrict potassium, phosphorus, and sodium intake. Avoid dense potassium foods common in Indian diets (spinach/palak, bananas, potatoes, coconut water). Limit overall protein intake strictly to clinical safety baselines to prevent elevated blood urea nitrogen (BUN) levels.",
    "high_uric_acid": "High Purine Restrictive Framework for Gout: Avoid high-purine plant elements prevalent in Indian vegetarian diets, specifically spinach (palak), mushrooms, gobhi, and heavy red lentils/beans (masoor, rajma, chole). Hydration telemetry must be held at an elevated tier to support renal clearance of uric acid.",
    "hyperlipidemia": "Cardiovascular Lipid Profile Management: Strictly limit saturated fats to less than 7% of total energy intake and completely eliminate trans-fats (Dalda/Vanaspati). Swap cooking mediums out for heart-healthy local unsaturated fats (MUFAs/PUFAs from mustard, groundnut, or sunflower oils). Restrict dietary cholesterol sources.",
    "lactose_intolerant": "Strictly eliminate all animal-derived dairy products. Replace dairy with plant-based alternatives like soy milk or almond milk. Ensure alternative calcium routing using dark leafy greens, millets like ragi, and sesame seeds (til).",
    "celiac_disease": "Strictly eliminate gluten proteins. Exclude standard whole wheat atta, maida, suji, dalia, and cross-contaminated ingredients. Ensure all grain suggestions are certified gluten-free local options like clean rice, amaranth (rajgira), ragi, bajra, or jowar. Note: Standard Indian 'Asafoetida' (hing) contains wheat flour as a binding agent and must be banned completely.",
    "peanut_allergy": "Anaphylaxis Warning Protocol: Forbid peanuts, peanut oil (singdana oil), and local peanut snacks like chikki. Ensure cooking mediums rely purely on mustard, sunflower, or olive oils processed on allergen-free machinery.",
    "soy_allergy": "Strictly exclude all soybean derivatives, including popular local vegetarian protein extenders like soy chunks and soya flour. Substitute with paneer (if non-dairy-restricted) or seed-based protein alternatives.",
    "veg": "Enforce a strict Indian Lacto-Vegetarian paradigm. Eliminate all animal flesh, seafood, and eggs. Rely purely on pulses, legumes, paneer, curd, and native dairy combinations to reach macronutrient protein targets.",
    "eggitarian": "Eliminate animal meats and seafood completely. Permits the inclusion of whole eggs and egg whites as primary bioavailable protein sources alongside traditional lacto-vegetarian options.",
    "vegan": "Enforce a strict 100% plant-based diet. Eliminate all animal flesh, dairy products, eggs, and animal-byproducts like honey or ghee. Rely on native legumes, grains, tofu, nuts, seeds, and local plant milks to fulfill macronutrient profiles.",
    "jain": "Enforce strict Jain vegetarian guidelines. In addition to eliminating all meats and eggs, completely exclude all underground root vegetables (rhizomes/tubers) including onions, garlic, ginger, potatoes, carrots, radish, and beetroot. Ensure meals utilize permitted green gourds (lauki, tori), grains, pulses, and dairy."
  },
